# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
# Executables without extension (anchored to repo root so they don't
# match the cmd/<service>/ source directories, which previously caused
# cmd/log-service/partition.go to be ignored and break CI builds)
/relay-gateway
/admin-api
/identity-service
/channel-service
/billing-service
/config-service
/log-service
/monitor-worker
/notify-worker
/migrate
# Short binary names produced by 'go build ./app/<svc>/cmd/<svc>/' without -o
/admin
/billing
/channel
/config
/identity
/log
/monitor
/notify

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# Generated OpenAPI document
openapi.yaml

# Generated protobuf code
api/**/*.pb.go

# env file
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Config files with sensitive data (use .env instead)
configs/*.yaml
!configs/config.yaml

# Certificates and keys
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.csr
certs/
keys/

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Local git worktrees
.worktrees/
test/e2e/e2e-test
web/node_modules
web/dist
web/.env
# Admin frontend build output. The Dockerfiles build the web in a
# dedicated web-builder stage and copy it into the embed path right
# before `go build`, so these built assets must never be tracked in
# git. `ADMIN_WEB_ROOT` can override the path at runtime; the
# `//go:embed all:static/web` directive is kept valid by `.gitkeep`.
app/admin/internal/server/static/web/*
!app/admin/internal/server/static/web/.gitkeep

cert/
.claude
# Local build/save outputs
dist/

# Subscription account import payloads (contain plaintext OAuth tokens)
subscription-account.*.payload.json

*.tar

.workbuddy